<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-443-039  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 443 039.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 16 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Computers seized in New York State Police action.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>McMullen, Barbara E.; McMullen, John F.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     New York (State). PoliceLegal IssuesComputer hackersComputer CrimesInvestigations.andO;Person:    Petel, Thomas (investigations).andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>COMPUTERS SEIZED IN NEW YORK STATE POLICE ACTION NEW YORK, NEW YORK, U.S.A.,andO;1990 AUG 16 (NB) -- The New York State Police today executed approximately 18search warrants in the New York metropolitan area and seized computerequipment pursuant to these search warrants.andP;  Details of the operations aresketchy at present but a Secret Service source who observed the operationtold Newsbytes that the persons on whom the warrants were served are allminors.andM;Newsbytes contacted one of the households where a warrant was executed andwas told that the equipment confiscated belonged to a 14-year-old, ThomasPetel.andP;  His mother, Ewa Petal, told Newsbytes that the state police hadseized computer equipment, documentation and diskettes and informed her thather son was being charged with computer tampering, first degree; computertampering, second degree and computer trespass, all violations of New Yorkstate law.andM;They were told, according to Mrs. Petel, that they would be called to NewYork Family Court in approximately 2 weeks.andP;  In the meantime, she wasinformed that the computer equipment would be impounded at New York City's62nd Precinct.andM;Mrs.andP;  Petal told Newsbytes that it is her understanding that the chargescenter around her son's connection to a system at a Community College inBellevue, Washington.andP;  Mrs. Petal said that her son had found the number ofthe college on a bulletin board with the explanation that it was a goodsystem for downloading game software.andP;  She said that her son signed on, used&quot;new.user&quot; as an identification and the password that he had received on theBBS and downloaded some games an music.andP;  She said that he also uploaded somegames for others to use.andM;Mrs.andP;  Petel said that she has since been informed by a state policeinvestigator that the system is for the sole use of students of the collegeand that her son was trespassing when he accessed it.andP;  When asked byNewsbytes if the incident with the community college was the sole reason forthe confiscation, she said &quot;yes, that's what they told us.&quot;andM;Attempts to obtain a statement from state police spokespersons were notsuccessful.andP;  Newsbytes was told that a press conference was scheduled forthis afternoon.andM;(Barbara E. McMullen andamp; John F. McMullen/19900816)</TEXT></DOC>